//TODO 6) What is exception and give some examples for exceptions?

-Arithmetic E,
-No Such Element E,
-Index Out of bound  E,
-(Thread.sleep) Interrupted E.

//TODO 7)How do you handle exceptions in Java?

-Try Catch  Finally
-throws keyword(method signature)

In Java, a "method signature" is part of the method declaration.
It's the combination of the method name and the parameter list.

public class Main {
  static void checkAge(int age) throws ArithmeticException {
    if (age < 18) {
      throw new ArithmeticException("Access denied - You must be at least 18 years old.");
    }
    else {
      System.out.println("Access granted - You are old enough!");
    }
  }

  public static void main(String[] args) {
    checkAge(15); // Set age to 15 (which is below 18...)
  }
}

